PrecisRegulations Amending the MEAT INSPECTION REGULATIONS, 1990 by making provision for the use of controlled atmosphere systems for stunning all food animals prior to slaughter, modifying the definition of "filler", allowing kidneys and sexual organs to be left in young chicken and duck carcasses, and by revising the protein content standard for meat roll.
RegistrationRegistration: SOR/ 1999-0369 Publication Date: 1999-10-13
Attachments
precis:
Regulations Amending the MEAT INSPECTION REGULATIONS, 1990 by making
provision for the use of controlled atmosphere systems for stunning all
food animals prior to slaughter, modifying the definition of "filler",
allowing kidneys and sexual organs to be left in young chicken and duck
carcasses, and by revising the protein content standard for meat roll.
